to set up python env for this retrieval_api and database

>>python -m venv venv
to activate environment
>>& D:/qwerty/.venv/Scripts/Activate.ps1

UPGRADE pip
>>python -m pip install --upgrade pip



REQUIRED PACKAGES
FastAPI + Uvicorn → for API

ChromaDB + embeddings → vector DB

SentenceTransformers → embeddings

psycopg2 → PostgreSQL

python-dotenv → for .env

pypdf → PDF reading

requests → optional, if Gemini needs it (usually in genai)

google-genai → Gemini API client

CMD IS
>>pip install fastapi uvicorn chromadb sentence-transformers psycopg2-binary python-dotenv pypdf google-genai


>>>  uvicorn retrieval_api:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 9000
this cmd is to run the retrieval_api

create a .env file in the same directory as retrieval_api.py and db.py
with the following content  
GEMINI_API_KEY=your gemini api key
CHROMA_DIR=./chroma_store
CHROMA_COLLECTION=policy_docs
GEMINI_MODEL=models/gemini-1.5-flash
GEMINI_ENDPOINT=https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models
TOP_K=3
MAX_PROMPT_CHARS=3000

as for the .env file in the parent directory, it should contain
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=1234
DB_DATABASE=policychat
PORT=8000
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key


when startting node backend ensure that you are using create environment
>>& D:/qwerty/.venv/Scripts/Activate.ps1

